cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and natural language processing, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories. The use of gated structures and recurrent neural networks also suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves multi-modal embedding, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the use of image features and attention mechanisms suggests that it may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
